comment_data.body: Sorry, the original was actually from @dpreussler.

Although mentioned by mistake above, still, I've tried on my side as well. 

Environment:
Flutter plugin 22.2.1 
Android Studio: 3.0.1 and 3.1.2

Mentioned behavior does not show up in the context menu, regardless of Kotlin or Java file. I'm sure Danny will provide an additional info.

_Edit:_
However, with the Flutter plugin version 24.2.1 (AS 3.1.2), the issue is reproduced. Hope it helps.
![screen shot 2018-05-15 at 21 57 17](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1321796/40080401-16e3e3ae-588b-11e8-9289-2e83583c9fa2.png)

I don't think that if IntelliJ lets us specify not to show such actions only for Flutter or Dart.

@pq @stevemessick ?

We have to check for a Flutter section in the pubspec.yaml during the action's update() method. At least, that's what we did for other menu items (like open-in-android-studio and open-in-xcode) that are specific to Flutter. It should work here, but I can't check ATM since my IDE sources are a mess.
Assigning to you Steve for when your IDE sources get untangled.

I sent the screenshot to @dpreussler, my current setup is:
Android Studio: 3.1.2
Flutter plugin: 24.2.1

This happens with other file types (android layout xml files etc)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5406413/40110520-725d2c02-5900-11e8-8a8e-3f37f195d29e.png)

The refactor button on the popup for creating a widget does nothing at least :D
Unassigning so @pq and @scheglov don't think they need to wait for me in case they have a chance to fix it soon.
I see what's up here.  Taking a look at a fix...

title: Flutter actions should not show for non-dart files?
